NLOAD              Fujinet CLI Tools›Load Binary File from Network Path››Usage:›NLOAD [/X] [Nx:]<path>››Description:››This tool loads/runs a standard ATARI ›binary load file, from the path›specified.››Parameters:››[/X] If set, NLOAD will clear all›memory from $0700 to $BFFF, before›starting the binary load. This can›allow certain stubborn programs›to work.››[Nx:] - the N: device to load from.›Optional, N1: is implied, ›if not specified.››[path] - Optional. Any additional›path information needed to find›the binary data. ›››Examples:››D1:NLOAD N:TNFS://myserver/myprog.xex››D1:NLOAD /X N:TNFS://foo/frogger.xex›››Interactive Mode:››For any DOS that does not support›command line parameters, such as›ATARI DOS 2, The following prompts›will be given:››CLEAR MEMORY? (Y/N)›Pressing Y or y will cause NLOAD›to clear all memory from $0700›to $BFFF, allowing certain stubborn›programs to work.››NETWORK LOAD FROM FILE?›This should be an N[x]: URL to a›ATARI binary load file on the›network.››--A Note about Clear Memory---------›This feature clears memory from ›$0700 to $BFFF, filling it with›zeroes. It does mean that any›FMS that may be in memory will be›wiped out, and the program will not›be able to return to DOS.›------------------------------------››--A note about the loader-----------›The Loader talks to FujiNet, directly›getting the unit number from the›devicespec provided by the user. It›sits in $0600, with some utility›functions at $0120. This gives a ›very high compatibility with many›binary load files, approximately›99% of them.›------------------------------------››--Using under SpartaDOS X-----------›NLOAD works fine under SpartaDOS X.›It also works with the X command,›if you need to disable the cartridge›------------------------------------›››››